.TH GHOSTTY-NEW-TAB 1
.SH NAME
ghostty-new-tab \- open a new Ghostty terminal tab and run a command in it.

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ghostty-new-tab
.IR "[command ...]"

.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B ghostty-new-tab
function uses AppleScript to bring the
.B Ghostty
terminal application to the foreground, open a new tab with
.BR Cmd+T ,
and type the given command followed by Return.

.SH OPTIONS
No flags. All arguments are treated as the command string to execute in the new tab.

.SH USAGE
Open a new tab and run a server:
.B ghostty-new-tab npm run dev

Open a new tab with no initial command:
.B ghostty-new-tab

.SH DEPENDENCIES
.IP \[bu] 2
.B Ghostty
terminal emulator must be running.
.IP \[bu] 2
.B osascript
(macOS only) \- this function is macOS-specific and will not work on other platforms.
.IP \[bu] 2
Accessibility permissions must be granted to the terminal running this function under System Settings > Privacy & Security > Accessibility.

.SH SEE ALSO
osascript(1)

.SH AUTHOR
Ramo Mislimi (mislimi.ramo@gmail.com)
